 of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#VM #JP\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>Ἰθι\u003Csupplied reason=\"undefined\" evidence=\"previouseditor\">ο\u003C/supplied>κασία ἥρ\u003Cunclear>υ\u003C/unclear>σα ἀγαθά\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\u003Cnote>Text checked against photograph in Vento\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"line 1\">\u003Cnote>Gabrici: ΙΘΙΟΚΑΣΙΑ ΗΡΥΣΑ ΑΓΑΘΑ; Manni Piraino: Ἰθι[. .]ασία ἥρ[υ]σα ἀγαθά\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\">\n                \u003Cp>\u003C!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div-->\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>Photograph in Vento is excellent and it is possible to see traces of almost the entire text, as originally read by Gabrici.\n                    \u003C!--painted inscr., with banqueting scene. Has another variant on the feminine form of heros, apparently, while the name is incomplete, but is, Bisi suggests, of Semitic, theophoric origin.-->\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"SEG\">\n                        \u003CcitedRange>50.0993\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.insc